					<div id="mw-content-text" class="mw-body-content"><div class="mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output" lang="en" dir="ltr"><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Not to be confused with <a href="/wiki/Natural_law" title="Natural law">Natural law</a>.</div>
<div class="shortdescription nomobile noexcerpt noprint searchaux" style="display:none">Concept in UK law</div>
<p class="mw-empty-elt">

</p>
<figure class="mw-default-size" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Raffael_053.jpg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Raffael_053.jpg/220px-Raffael_053.jpg" decoding="async" width="220" height="169" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Raffael_053.jpg/330px-Raffael_053.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Raffael_053.jpg/440px-Raffael_053.jpg 2x" data-file-width="2536" data-file-height="1946" /></a><figcaption>A <a href="/wiki/Tondo_(art)" title="Tondo (art)">tondo</a> of an allegory of <a href="/wiki/Lady_Justice" title="Lady Justice">justice</a> (1508) by <a href="/wiki/Raphael" title="Raphael">Raphael</a> in the <a href="/wiki/Raphael_Rooms" title="Raphael Rooms">Stanza della Segnatura</a> (Room of the <a href="/wiki/Apostolic_Signatura" title="Apostolic Signatura">Apostolic Signatura</a>) of the <a href="/wiki/Apostolic_Palace" title="Apostolic Palace">Apostolic Palace</a>, <a href="/wiki/Vatican_City" title="Vatican City">Vatican City</a></figcaption></figure>
