<li id="cite_note-59"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-59">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><i>Front Row Investment Holdings (Singapore) Pte. Ltd. v. Daimler South East Asia Pte. Ltd.</i> [2010] SGHC 80 at para. 31, H.C. (Singapore); see also <i>R v Industrial Injuries Commissioner, ex parte Howarth</i> (1968) 4 K.I.R. 621; <i>Kay Swee Pin</i>, p. 806, para. 7: "[I]f a tribunal, after the close of the hearing, comes into possession of further evidence, the party affected should be invited to comment upon it".</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-SEF_Construction-60"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-SEF_Construction_60-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-SEF_Construction_60-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><i>SEF Construction Pte. Ltd. v. Skoy Connected Pte. Ltd.</i> [2010] 1 S.L.R. 733 at 757, para. 58.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-61"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-61">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><i>Kok Seng Chong v. Bukit Turf Club</i> [1992] 3 S.L.R.(R.) 772, H.C. (Singapore).</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-ex_parte_Tarrant-62"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-ex_parte_Tarrant_62-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-ex_parte_Tarrant_62-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><i>R v Secretary of State for Home Department, ex parte Tarrant</i> [1985] 1 <a href="/wiki/Queens_Bench_Law_Reports" class="mw-redirect" title="Queens Bench Law Reports">QB</a> 251, <a href="/wiki/Divisional_Court_(England_and_Wales)" class="mw-redirect" title="Divisional Court (England and Wales)">Divisional Court</a> (England &amp; Wales).</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-63"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-63">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><i>Doresamy v. Public Services Commission</i> [1971] 2 <i>Malayan Law Journal</i> 127, <a href="/wiki/High_Courts_of_Malaysia" class="mw-redirect" title="High Courts of Malaysia">High Court</a> (Malaysia).</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-64"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-64">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><i>Ho Paul v. Singapore Medical Council</i> [2008] 2 S.L.R.(R.) 780, H.C. (Singapore).</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Rajeevan_Edakalavan-65"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Rajeevan_Edakalavan_65-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Rajeevan_Edakalavan_65-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><i>Rajeevan Edakalavan v. Public Prosecutor</i> [1998] 1 S.L.R.(R.) 10, H.C. (Singapore).</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-66"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-66">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><i>Re Siah Mooi Guat</i> [1988] 2. S.L.R.(R.) 165 at 178–179, para. 34, H.C. (Singapore).</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-ex_parte_Shaw-67"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-ex_parte_Shaw_67-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-ex_parte_Shaw_67-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><i>R v Northumberland Compensation Appeal Tribunal, ex parte Shaw</i> [1952] 1 <a href="/wiki/Kings_Bench_Law_Reports" class="mw-redirect" title="Kings Bench Law Reports">KB</a> 338, <a href="/wiki/Court_of_Appeal_(England_and_Wales)" title="Court of Appeal (England and Wales)">Court of Appeal</a> (England &amp; Wales).</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-68"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-68">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFKeith_Frank_Goodfellow1971" class="citation cs2">Keith Frank Goodfellow (1971), <i>Administration under Law: A Report by <a href="/wiki/JUSTICE" class="mw-redirect" title="JUSTICE">JUSTICE</a></i>, London: Stevens, p.&#160;23, <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-420-43710-5" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-420-43710-5"><bdi>978-0-420-43710-5</bdi></a></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Administration+under+Law%3A+A+Report+by+JUSTICE&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.pages=23&amp;rft.pub=Stevens&amp;rft.date=1971&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-420-43710-5&amp;rft.au=Keith+Frank+Goodfellow&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ANatural+justice" class="Z3988"></span>.</span>
